'''Philbert Aimé Mbabazi Sharangabo''' (wavutse 1990), ni umukinnyi wa firime wo mu [[Rwanda]]<ref>https://www.newtimes.co.rw/section/read/188273</ref> .  Yakoze filimi nyinshi harimo, ''The Liberators,'' ''Versus'' and ''I Got My Things And Left.''<ref>http://www.torinofilmlab.it/people/6566-philbert-aime-mbabazi-sharangabo</ref> 

== Ubuzima bwite ==
Yavutse mu 1990 i [[Kigali]], mu [[Rwanda]] .

== Umwuga ==
Mbabazi yabonye impamyabumenyi y'icyiciro cya kabiri cya kaminuza mu ishami rya sinema yakuye muri kaminuza y’ubuhanzi n’ubushakashatsi i Geneve (UMUTWE - Genève, Haute école d'art et de design)  .  Mugihe cyishuri, yakoze firime ebyiri ''The Liberators'' na ''Versus''<ref>https://iffr.com/en/persons/philbert-aim%C3%A9-mbabazi-sharangabo</ref><ref>https://iffr.com/en/persons/philbert-aim%C3%A9-mbabazi-sharangabo</ref> . Filime zombi zerekanwe mu birori byinshi bya firime birimo Vision du Réel Nyon, Internationale Kurzfilmtage Winterthur, Tampere, Oberhausen na Uppsala Festival Festival.  Amaze kubona impamyabumenyi muri 2017, yasubiye mu [[Rwanda]]<ref>http://www.torinofilmlab.it/people/6566-philbert-aime-mbabazi-sharangabo</ref>.

Muri 2019, yayoboye filime ngufi''I Got My Things And Left'' yatsindiye igihembo kinini mu iserukiramuco mpuzamahanga rya firime rya Oberhausen. Iyi filime yerekanwe mu iserukiramuco rya firime rirenga 20 nk'Iserukiramuco mpuzamahanga rya Filimi rya Rotterdam, International Kurzfilmtage Winterthur, Internationale Kurzfimtage Winterthur, Genda Nijmegen, Indie Lisboa na ISFF Hamburg, FIFF Namur n'ibindi<ref>https://igihe.com/imyidagaduro/article/ibyishimo-kuri-seburikoko-na-nikuze-begukanye-ibihembo-muri-mashariki-amafoto</ref><ref>https://inyarwanda.com/inkuru/108271/ines-girihirwe-yashyikirijwe-igihembo-yegukanye-mu-iserukiramuco-rya-filime-muri-zanzibar-108271.html</ref> . yatangije isosiyete ikora firime yitwa 'Imitana Productions' ifite icyicaro i [[Kigali]], mu [[Rwanda]]. Nyuma yaje gukora filime ye ya mbere ya ''Republika'' (Spectrum<ref>https://www.iamafilm.com/index.php/Mbabazi</ref>).  

